{"key":"processedPost-8568347","value":{"id":8568347,"first":8567931,"last":8568533,"when":1214529726,"utime":"06/27/08 04:22 AM","content":"You don't case the bottom, and microwaves are horrible for mycology unless it's brand new.&nbsp; You also don't sterilize casing mix because it's much more susceptible to contamination if sterilized.&nbsp; That's why we pasteurize casing and substrate mixes.<br /><br />There's actually little to be gained by casing pf cakes.&nbsp; They're already 2/3 vermiculite.&nbsp; They make nice spawn to bulk substrates, or fruited as cakes.&nbsp; You'll rarely get more total product from cased cakes as from using the dunk and roll tek and fruiting them for a few flushes as cakes.<br />RR","title":"Re: 20 Gal Long Aquarium Terrarium","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}